##"She's not afraid of us! " This was how Zhanjiang, a fast-moving city, treated its tourists

Micro-signal. NBWEEKLY

Introduction of function, new media with temperature

"What do you say we keep this group together? "

"Good! The epidemic is unrelenting, and Xuwen County is here to make love and never break up! "

By Liang Jinhong, Gan Linan, Han Fenglan, editor | Xiaodou

Recently, Lao Gan Ma and Niu Lan Shan Baijiu from Xuwen County supermarkets in Guangdong Province suddenly became hot sellers. They were packed into the biggest plastic bags by volunteers and sent to Huatong hotel one after another.

Xuwen County, at the southernmost tip of mainland China, is the only place to pass through Qiongzhou Strait.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xuwen County, located at the southernmost tip of mainland China, was the "starting port of the Han Dynasty Sea route of Silk Road" .

Since January 25, Haikou has suspended Hubei tourists from visiting the island, leaving scores of Wuhan residents stranded in the small southern city.

I'm in a quandary. I've hit a wall

Chen and his family live in the Guanggu district of Wuhan, across the Yangtze River from the South China Seafood Wholesale Market, where the outbreak began.

When the family left Wuhan on Jan. 17, there were few reports of COVID-19 pneumonia. "We didn't say the virus could be transmitted from person to person, so we didn't care too much. "

The seven members of their family set out in batches, traveling first to Guangzhou to visit relatives, and then to Hainan by car for the Spring Festival.

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, Chen and his family left Guangzhou and drove to Xuwen County, intending to take a ferry from the port to Hainan.

"On the first day of the year, it was raining all day. " They arrived in Xuwen County at 10 pm. The family was tired and decided to stay in Xuwen for the night.

By this time, the city had been closed, the epidemic Meng Meng, Hubei a car, Wuhan people overnight became an unwelcome group.

Chen Ming found a hotel, the front desk heard that they are from Hubei, refused to check them in, they go to the Huatong hotel. Chen Ming searched the hotel's location on the map, but he couldn't find it.

So Chen Ming decided to go to the harbor to have a look.

On the way, a friend called to say that the people of Wuhan, Hubei Province, on the other side of Haikou, had been quarantined.

His wife, Yang Li, worries about being quarantined from other recent travelers to Hubei in case they get infected.

Helpless, a family and back to town, Chen Ming remembered the hotel in Guangzhou, still call every day to track whether they have fever, cough symptoms, maybe there is a chance.

But over the phone, the hotel has refused to Hubei Wuhan residents to check in, and repeatedly apologized.

The home virus comes menacingly, the panic of strange land, refuse also be expected.

"If we had known the epidemic would be so serious, we would have stayed to advance and retreat with the people of Wuhan, " Yang told Nandu weekly. "everyone has old people, children and worries. "

Chen Ming and his family finally accepted the fact that they were under centralized quarantine. They wanted to go to Haikou to be quarantined.

At 1 am on the 26th, Chen Ming drove back to the wharf, near which a doctor told them not to go to Haikou, saying that people from Wuhan had been quarantined and many patients with fever had been found there.

The mood of the family is low to the bottom, "neither into nor out, we feel so helpless for the first time. "

Huang Ai, a truck driver who was going to Sanya to load mangoes, was also forced to stop at Xuwen County, a man from Xiangyang, Hubei Province, who arrived in Xuwen County on January 17.

When Xu Wen arrived, Huang Ai had not yet heard about the epidemic. Later, she saw the news reports. At that time, she only felt that it was like the flu and would not be very serious. Only when the city of Wuhan was shut down did he realize the seriousness of the matter.

Huang stopped his car near Mulan Avenue to eat and live in the car. On the 22nd, he posted a video of himself cooking in the car on his friends'circle. His license plate is also from Hubei, but it was never reported.

"large number of Wuhan vehicles detained in Zhanjiang. " 

As elsewhere, Zhanjiang, an obscure third-tier city, was initially panicked when it welcomed this particular group of guests.

Some residents spotted a lot of Hubei cars parked downstairs and on the side of the road. They took photos and sent them to friends' circles. "I've seen more cars from Hubei coming to Zhanjiang than I have seen in three years. The hardest hit areas are in Vanda and Jinsha Bay! ".

Weibo also exploded, with hot topics such as "cars in Zhanjiang involving Hubei" and "a large number of Wuhan people in Zhanjiang" appearing. Some Netizens said that a large number of Hubei vehicles were preparing to go to Hainan, the island closure left them stranded in the city of Zhanjiang, in Xuwen and around Leizhou.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On Weibo, the topic of "cars in Zhanjiang involving Hubei Province" became a hot topic.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Calls from the Centers for Disease Control and prevention spread through wechat groups.

Zhanjiang CDC telephone number in Wechat, Weibo widely spread, friends and relatives have told each other to see Hubei license vehicles to the Zhanjiang CDC "report. ". For a while, the entire city of Zhanjiang was under siege, with citizens on high alert, ready to intercept cars in the streets.

Since January 26,2020, the office of the Leading Group for the prevention and control of COVID-19 pneumonia in Xuwen County issued a notice on January 25, a 14-day intensive medical health observation was carried out on passengers from Hubei Province, especially Wuhan, passing through the sea from Hainan at the Huatong hotel on Xuhai Avenue, Xuwen County.

At this point, Chen Ming family has been in the car for more than ten hours, we are exhausted.

Glimmers of despair, "she is not afraid of us"

"Can not let the child and the old man continue to stay overnight in the car, " Chen Ming decided to call 110 for help. After the police guidance, he finally found the Huatong hotel.

Chen Ming recalls, there was also a night shift at the front desk staff, is a young girl. The girl told them that there was room available, asked if they had eaten, and left several boxes at the front desk.

For the Chen family, the girl's enthusiasm, after their repeated rejection, appears extremely warm and precious.

"She is not afraid of us" , Yang Li is moved by this.

Knowing that Huatong hotel has become a central observation point for tourists in Hubei Province, many hotel staff are reluctant to stay for fear of being infected with COVID-19, so who will do the job of rehousing and serving Hubei tourists?

Xu Chengcong, affectionately known as sister Xu, took the lead in signing up to help resettle the passengers. Xu, a 50-year-old Hottie from Hunan Province, came to Zhanjiang 25 years ago to do business. Xuwen County is her adopted hometown.

Shortly after 10 pm on the 25th, Xu Jie saw a message from the wechat group of the Xuwen County Volunteer Service Federation: Urgently Summon 10 volunteers to take part in the resettlement service for tourists in Hubei.

She did not hesitate, the next morning, Xu Jie Volunteer Association of the four volunteers to the huatong hotel report.

On the other hand, notice, guide Hubei Hotel guests to stay in the work also continues to be synchronized.

Around 3 p.m. on the 26th, two police cars pulled up next to Huang's car and told him to stay at the Huatong hotel.

Huang Ai drove the truck to the hotel entrance, next to the parking lot full of Hubei brand cars, has been unable to stop the big truck.

But under, Huang Ai drove around the county seat to turn a few times, at the roadside randomly found a place to cope with the night.

The next day, after the county government coordination, finally found a place to park the truck, Huang Ai this just relax, sat on a special bus, check into the Huatong hotel.

Thus, the Huatong Hotel, located on Xuhai Avenue, less than 4 km from Hai'an County Quay, became a destination for more than 150 Hubei tourists.

After Chen Ming and Huang Ai, there were more and more tourists from Hubei. On Feb. 1, the southern metropolis weekly asked Xuwen County again about his hotel and saw a notice.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
That volunteers have been setting up

At first, the volunteers were all flustered, and none of them had ever worked as a hotel maid.

Changing sheets, checking in, changing beds, arranging meals, cleaning hotel lobbies, and sweating for less than an hour, breathing hot air that makes masks soggy.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Volunteers work at the front desk of the hotel. (photo provided by interviewee)

The phones at the front desk were ringing off the hook. There were Xuwen County signs to check in, Hubei tourists who had been turned down several times by other hotels, and people who weren't from Hubei asking about hotel rooms.

Many tourists have been running several places, have not found willing to accept the Hubei People's hotel, heart accumulated a lot of grievances, only looking forward to leaving early.

Volunteer Ah you told reporters that these days he is doing the most convincing work, "since come, then settle" has become almost a catchphrase.

Hubei People Love Spicy food. Xu Jie took advantage of the lunch break to go home and fry a big pot of red pepper. She drove back to help in less than half an hour, "It's a waste of time to go back and forth every day. I'll go home and clean up and move to a hotel tonight. "

My hands are busy, my eyes are busy. The wechat group, titled "Hubei Family: We shoulder together if we have difficulties" , keeps popping up messages: Can't turn on the TV? Why isn't the room getting wi-fi? Do you have any more garbage bags? WHO DO I call to change the sheets?

In the evening, someone from the group sent a message: "there is no hot water on the seventh floor, " "the water temperature is very low, we still have two children, can not wash. " Night Shift of a Yu door to door to solve the problem.

"We don't know how to fix it, but we will, and we will show them that we are serious about what they want, " he said. "It turns out that they are just turning the tap on the wrong way around. " And addressing new needs in the WECHAT CROWD:

"which one of you wants another godmother? "

"One for 307. "

"bring me two, please! "

"And two bottles of Niulanshan, 42 degrees. "

Occupying the main content of group chat, is the list of goods needed by Hubei residents: a paper, a can of milk powder, two soap, a black toothpaste box, two bottles of medical alcohol, two wash basins

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A list of materials and materials needed by tourists in Hubei Province.

Take the room as the unit, each household sends the representative in turn to link the Dragon, lists the material which today needs. The list is very long, with your finger down four or five times to be able to turn over, the customer demand is the most mask and disinfection water.

"Hubei Family" group meeting and not disbanding

In addition to eating and living these trifles, Hubei tourists are most concerned about the question is: After 14 days can go home? What happens when you get somewhere else and you're quarantined?

According to research conducted by various departments of the Xuwen County government, travellers from Hubei who have spent 14 days in designated hotels and have not developed fever, cough or other suspected symptoms of infection will receive health certificates issued by the Xuwen County government.

The volunteers told the group the good news, and the next moment the crowd was flooded with "yes! " And thumbs-up emojis.

The reassured traveler then began to think: can't leave the hotel, how to spend the long two weeks?

Someone proposed the idea of playing cards, which was echoed by everyone. Volunteers were asked to buy a few decks of playing cards when they went to the supermarket, along with five or six bottles of 42-degree Niulanshan liquor and a dozen packs of cigarettes.

Many of the guests are with children, some are going to primary school, but these days, watching television, playing mobile phones seriously overtime, parents worry that the children play distracted.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Elementary School math test paper uploaded by Liu Wen and his wife

Liu Wen and his wife found an electronic version of the primary school math final comprehensive test paper, and asked volunteers to help print, other parents see also in the group after the speech: "Can we also print a copy? "

Mr. Liu and his wife set off from Wuhan on Jan. 16 with their two children, both of whom are engaged in physical education and training, with special emphasis on their sons'education. Every morning from 9:30 to 11:30, is Liu Wen to the children's story time; after dinner, she will take the sons to do exercise, to help digestion, after all, "these days have been locked up hard enough. ".

Liu Wen was pleasantly surprised to find that his eldest son became sensible. The elder son used to love fighting with his younger brother over jealousy, but yesterday, when Liu Wen finished feeding his younger son breakfast and preparing his own meal, he looked back and saw that the elder son was telling his younger brother about the "origin of rice" in a dignified manner. The two children asked and answered, liu Wen thought this picture was very precious.

A you, a volunteer, understood the hotel's Hubei residents. "after all, they are not professionals, and we can understand the fear of the unknown. We volunteer here, and our neighbors warn us to be careful. ".

When interviewed by Nandu weekly, the people staying at the Xuwen Huatong hotel showed no symptoms of infection, and the county government also sent 10 sets of protective clothing to the volunteers.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The supplies the locals sent to the hotel. (photo provided by interviewee)

After word of Xu's volunteer work spread, locals also brought in fruit, vegetables, eggs, beer and noodles of various flavors, in large and small boxes of nearly 50 cases, arranged in a row, piled high, the front desk of the hotel was covered.

People and cars are suffering because of the epidemic. Huang Ai, a truck driver, is most worried that the family needs to pay over 4,000 yuan a month in mortgage payments and over 13,000 yuan in car loans. His wife stays at home full-time to take care of their two children. They have no savings, and after 14 days of isolation, where to make money first.

At 22:48 pm on the 27th, the sleepless Huang Ai sat on the bed in her room and typed a line with her mobile phone, to the Wechat Group: "Thank you very much for the help of all volunteers, I come from Xiangyang, Hubei, our city always welcome you to visit after the epidemic. "

Volunteer a you proposal: "We say, after this group does not dissolve how? "

"DO NOT DISPERSE! "

(at the request of the interviewee, Chen Ming and Yang Li are assumed names.)
